The paper presents a new technique for approximate inference in Bayesian networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses experiments with Gaussian mixture models, which is a common topic in statistical learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
